Regarding Iksars: <br>
<br>
I have to agree with the Iksars on this thread. It's not my favorite race, but I've played an Iksar before....and I *always* read all the racial histories on a race before I play it on EQ. And on this point, I agree with the lizards here, I never heard of any influence of Innoruuk outside of the fact that.... late in Venril Sathir's life (long after he established total conquest in his Sebilis Empire) he eventually wanted lich-like immortality which Innoruuk gladly tempted him with. Other than that, what Verant's official release history would indicate is that for the earlier part of Venril's reign, both himself and his Iksar nation had typically worshipped their creator Cazic. <br>
<br>
In fact it was even clear that his son, the crown prince and heir to the Iksar empire, had thought that Venril had gone insane for succumbing to Innoruuk.....kinda like a deal with the devil sorta thing. That's why Venril's son tried to kill him. Makes perfect sense. <br>
<br>
Now, you may be perfectly correct in saying that Verant's beta material may have stated otherwise.... but if beta material differs from release material.... then it boils down to the question: <br>
<br>
What is considered canon EQ history? <br>
What is considered non-canon EQ history? <br>
<br>
Does Verant's beta material count as &quot;canon&quot; history for game lore purposes? Don't get me wrong, I think youre a great historian for writing this Compendium.  <br>
<br>
